25/01/2004
PARIS, France -- In an interview with the French newspaper <I>Le Figaro</i> on Friday (23 January), Macedonian Prime Minister Branko Crvenkovski said his country's main challenge is to enter the EU as soon as possible. Skopje has several years to achieve results that Western Europe took centuries to accomplish, Crvenkovski said, adding that the biggest test ahead was the decision on Kosovo's status. The prime minister also spoke with the BBC, saying that Skopje plans to submit its application for EU membership by the end of February. (MIA - 23/01/04)
